document_data.Background:
As a place that existed outside time and space, the castle could shift through time, trapping within its ruins creatures and [[adventurer]]s from any time period of either [[Abeir]] and [[Toril]]. The ghosts of the members of the [[Garrandar (family)|Garrandar]] family were also trapped forever in Darkturret.{{Cite organized play/LFR/Stir Not the World's Doom|8-17}}

Among the rooms of Darkturret, there was one connected to a time period when the goddess [[Mystryl]] was still alive,{{Cite organized play/LFR/Stir Not the World's Doom|9}} another room connected to the year [[569 DR]],{{Cite organized play/LFR/Stir Not the World's Doom|11}} and another to the year [[2421 DR]].{{Cite organized play/LFR/Stir Not the World's Doom|10}}

Another room had [[magic]]al crystal spheres that allowed a person to see specific historical events. Among the events showed by the spheres were:{{Cite organized play/LFR/Stir Not the World's Doom|13-14}}
* The creation of the [[yuan-ti]] and [[naga]] races in the [[Days of Thunder]].
* The first moments of [[Karsus's Folly]].
* The assassination of [[Leira]] at the hands of [[Cyric]].
* The first moments of the Spellplague.
